                            <comment id="14604453" author="JIRAUSER19600" created="Wed, 16 Aug 2023 09:30:54 -0700"  >[~davleopo] There&amp;#39;s a standardized way to use random values in tests.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
In the test tags add&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;* @key randomness&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;* @library /test/lib&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;* @build jdk.test.lib.RandomFactory&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
In the imports add&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
import jdk.test.lib.RandomFactory;&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
and use it as in&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
Random rnd = RandomFactory.getRandom()&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This will print the seed to stdout</comment>
